techmeme.title: Oppo launches the Find N5, the world's thinnest foldable at 8.93mm closed and 4.21mm open, with IPX6, X8, and X9 ratings, in Europe and Asia for ~$1,870 (Dominic Preston/The Verge)
Tokyo-based Sakana AI details its AI CUDA Engineer, which it says can speed up AI training and inference by 10x to 100x by "breeding" efficient instructions (Nikkei Asia)
Meta says Mark Zuckerberg went to the US Capitol on February 19 to lobby Senators on AI and talk about issues like US tech leadership and ending DEI programs (Emily Birnbaum/Bloomberg)
Sources: Google is close to deciding on locations in India for its first physical retail stores outside the US; the company currently has five stores (Aditya Kalra/Reuters)
Rabbit R1 maker Rabbit demos its "generalist Android agent", showing it controlling apps on a tablet, building on its LAM Playground, a "generalist web agent" (Wes Davis/The Verge)
